videos.description: Iowa State quarterback Kyle Kempt is hit while throwing to Allen Lazard, who adjusts his route to make a diving catch for a 22-yard gain.
videos.headline: Lazard comes back to make diving catch

videos.description: Kyle Kempt connects with Matthew Eaton for a 17-yard touchdown to give Iowa State the lead.
videos.headline: Kempt finds Eaton for the Cyclones' first TD

videos.description: Kyle Hicks runs for 22 yards in style to move into Iowa State's territory.
videos.headline: Hicks cuts through the defense for TCU

videos.description: Kyle Kempt throws one up for Allen Lazard, who makes a fantastic catch to get Iowa State into the red zone.
videos.headline: Lazard gets up for 30-yard catch

videos.description: Kyle Kempt finds Hakeem Butler at the back of the end zone on a four-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Butler keeps feet inbounds for an Iowa State TD

videos.description: TCU head coach Gary Patterson says his team can improve on first down by being more patient as it enters the half down 14-0 to Iowa State.
videos.headline: Patterson: 'We need to be more patient'

videos.description: KaVontae Turpin starts off the third quarter with a 94-yard kick return touchdown to get the Horned Frogs on the board.
videos.headline: Turpin returns kick for TCU TD

videos.description: Kenny Hill throws an interception just outside the end zone and Brian Peavy returns it 70 yards for Iowa State.
videos.headline: Cyclones pick off Hill in red zone

videos.description: Kenny Hill loses the ball as he's taken down by JaQuan Bailey deep inside Iowa State's territory in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Hill fumbles away key red-zone chance

videos.description: Marcel Spears Jr. intercepts Kenny Hill with just over a minute to go to seal the upset for Iowa State.
videos.headline: Iowa State picks off TCU to seal upset

videos.description: Iowa State head coach Matt Campbell couldn't be more proud of his team's defensive effort in their upset win against TCU.
videos.headline: Campbell praises gutsy defense

videos.description: Emmanuel Acho and Chip Kelly break down Iowa State's big win over Iowa State and how this might be bad news for the Big 12 in the College Football Playoff.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Big 12 in trouble after TCU's loss) 2017/10/28 CFB Live

videos.headline: Big 12 in trouble after TCU's loss

videos.description: The No. 3 Horned Frogs lose the ball three times in the second half en route to a 14-7 loss to the No. 25 Cyclones.
videos.headline: Turnovers plague TCU in loss to Iowa State
